<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-419-128  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 419 128.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  April 30 1990 n588 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fuzzy logic optimizes TV image. (Sony's Advanced Signal Correctioncircuit) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Doherty, Richard.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Sony Corp's Advanced Signal Correction (ASC) circuit is the firstconsumer electronic use of a fuzzy logic expert system foroptimizing the picture image on a new family of advancedTV/monitor receivers.andP;  The ASC makes real-time changes in picturecontrast, hue, color saturation and picture detail.andP;  The changesare based on a combination of pre-stored image rules and theconsumer's individual image preferences.andP;  Decisions are made 60times per second based on 248 individual regions of the NTSC videoimage.andP;  The user establishes the quality of the contrast, colordepth and picture detail and the ASC circuitry modifies the imagecontrols to deliver the best possible picture.andP;  A Sound RetrievalSystem (SRS) is also available to enrich TV sound broadcasts.andP;  TheASC feature is built into new 27-inch and 32-inch XBR colortelevision sets.andP;  Prices for the sets are $1,450 and $2,799respectively.andP;  They will ship in the summer of 1990.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sony Corp. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    SNE.andO;Product:   Sony Advanced Signal Correction Circuit (Integrated circuit)(product introduction).andO;Topic:     Television EquipmentTelevision SetsFuzzy SetsImage Enhancement.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>